pter 11. (If you=E2=80=99re just going to sell all your stuff and liquidate=
, you file Chapter 7.)  Chapter 15 is the bit of the US Bankruptcy Code tha=
t governs international bankruptcies where  the *main* proceedings are some=
where else: =E2=80=9CGenerally, a chapter 15 case is ancillary to a primary=
 proceeding brought in another country, typically the debtor's home country=
.=E2=80=9D


