10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">FTX</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t want to minimize the likelihoo=
d of intentional fraud and theft. Stuff seems bad. But I want to say that t=
he story of FTX=C2=A0<em>also=C2=A0</em>reads like what would happen if you=
 and a few of your college friends set up a gigantic international financia=
l exchange after like a year or two of working in finance. Oh, your friends=
 are smart. They have decent intuitions about financial stuff; they have go=
od ideas for what products to trade and how to trade them; they can code up=
 a good-looking website. But do they have hard-won expertise, built up over=
 many years, in accounting controls and business processes for running a gi=
ant organization? Are they excited about making sure all the paperwork is c=
orrect? No, that stuff is boring. Your friends are traders and engineers, n=
ot accountants and compliance officers. Also there just aren=E2=80=99t that=
 <em>many=C2=A0</em>of them, and they are running a huge exchange; they are=
 too busy for paperwork. They move fast and break things. They break so man=
y things.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/29730538.256530/aHR0cHM6Ly9wYWNlci1kb2N1bWVudHMuczMu=
YW1hem9uYXdzLmNvbS8zMy8xODg0NTAvMDQyMDIwNjQ4MTk3LnBkZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB6a50da72" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> first day declaration</a> from the chief executive =
officer of FTX Trading Ltd., John J. Ray III, in FTX=E2=80=99s Chapter 11 b=
ankruptcy case in Delaware. Ray has not been the CEO of FTX for long, =E2=
=80=9Chaving accepted this position in the early morning hours of November =
11, 2022,=E2=80=9D and imagine getting=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>4:30 a.m. ph=
one call. Before that, Ray had nothing to do with FTX; its CEO was its 30-y=
ear-old founder, Sam Bankman-Fried. But Ray is an old hand at big bankruptc=
ies =E2=80=94 he has =E2=80=9Cbeen the Chief Restructuring Officer or Chief=
 Executive Officer in several of the largest corporate failures in history,=
=E2=80=9D including Enron Corp. =E2=80=94=C2=A0so he got the call here. =E2=
=80=9CI am over the age of 18,=E2=80=9D says Ray in his declaration, and it=
 seems relevant.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgro=
und-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Because the gist of this declaration is that, =
while Ray definitely=C2=A0doesn=E2=80=99t minimize the likelihood of intent=
ional fraud and theft, mostly he is aghast at the children who ran FTX and =
had no idea what they were doing:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Never in my career have I seen suc=
h a complete failure of corporate controls and such a complete absence of t=
rustworthy financial information as occurred here. From compromised systems=
 integrity and faulty regulatory oversight abroad, to the concentration of =
control in the hands of a very small group of inexperienced, unsophisticate=
d and potentially compromised individuals, this situation is unprecedented.=
</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He=E2=80=99s never seen anything this bad in h=
is career, and he saw Enron! Where to begin? With the emojis?</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors did not have the type =
of disbursement controls that I believe are appropriate for a business ente=
rprise. For example, employees of the FTX Group submitted payment requests =
through an on-line =E2=80=98chat=E2=80=99 platform where a disparate group =
of supervisors approved disbursements by responding with personalized emoji=
s.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is not best practices, but I guess it is,=
 like,=C2=A0you-and-a-few-of-your-buddies practices. If you and your friend=
s set up a financial exchange and overnight it became gigantic, and you wer=
e like =E2=80=9CI would like to pay $6=C2=A0million for a Super Bowl ad for=
 our suddenly gigantic business,=E2=80=9D and your boss said =E2=80=9Cokay =
submit a request in our payments system and the marketing committee will ap=
prove it and then we will have the payments department disburse the money,=
=E2=80=9D that would feel boring and formal. If you just type in the chat =
=E2=80=9CI would like to pay $6 million for a Super Bowl ad,=E2=80=9D and s=
ome more senior person =E2=80=94=C2=A0not your boss, just =E2=80=9Ca dispar=
ate group of supervisors=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 gives you a thumbs-up, you migh=
t be like =E2=80=9Coh, cool, what a cool company this is, we do Big Busines=
s based on emojis in the chat.=E2=80=9D But it is not cool, it turns out.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Certainly it makes Ray=E2=80=99s job hard. His=
 basic job, as the CEO of a bankruptcy estate, is to figure out how much st=
uff FTX has, figure out how much it owes to its customers and other credito=
rs, and parcel out the stuff among the customers and creditors. But all of =
that is basically impossible, because FTX kept disorganized halfhearted rec=
ords of its stuff, its customers, its creditors, its employees<a class=3D"f=
ootnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !impor=
tant; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a> and everything else. It is hard even to tell what =E2=80=9CFTX=E2=80=
=9D was; Ray=E2=80=99s declaration describes four =E2=80=9Csilos=E2=80=9D =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0international crypto exchange FTX.com (the =E2=80=9CDotcom S=
ilo=E2=80=9D), US-based crypto exchange FTX.us (the =E2=80=9CWRS Silo,=E2=
=80=9D because the top-level legal entity there seems to be West Realm Shir=
es Inc.), crypto market-making and trading firm Alameda Research LLC, and F=
TX=E2=80=99s venture capital arm =E2=80=94=C2=A0all of which had overlappin=
g ownership, unclear legal entities and intertwined financial accounts.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So here is how FTX, once reputed to be one of =
the most sophisticated crypto exchanges, kept its crypto:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FTX Group did not keep appropriate books a=
nd records, or security controls, with respect to its digital assets. Mr. B=
ankman-Fried and [Alameda co-founder Gary]=C2=A0Wang controlled access to d=
igital assets of the main businesses in the FTX Group (with the exception o=
f LedgerX, regulated by the CFTC, and certain other regulated and/or licens=
ed subsidiaries). Unacceptable=C2=A0management practices included the use o=
f an unsecured group email account as the root user to access confidential =
private keys and critically sensitive data for the FTX Group companies arou=
nd the world, the absence of daily reconciliation of positions on the block=
chain, the use of software to conceal the misuse of customer funds, the sec=
ret exemption of Alameda from certain aspects of FTX.com=E2=80=99s auto-liq=
uidation protocol, and the absence of independent governance as between Ala=
meda (owned 90% by Mr. Bankman-Fried and 10% by Mr. Wang) and the Dotcom Si=
lo (in which third parties had invested).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors have located and secured only a fr=
action of the digital assets of the FTX Group that they hope to recover in =
these Chapter 11 Cases. The Debtors have secured in new cold wallets approx=
imately $740 million of cryptocurrency that the Debtors believe is attribut=
able to either the WRS, Alameda and/or Dotcom Silos. The Debtors have not y=
et been able to determine how much of this cryptocurrency is allocable to e=
ach Silo, or even if such an allocation can be determined. These balances e=
xclude cryptocurrency not currently under the Debtors=E2=80=99 control as a=
 result of (a) at least $372 million of unauthorized transfers initiated on=
 the Petition Date, during which time the Debtors immediately began moving =
cryptocurrency into cold storage to mitigate the risk to the remaining cryp=
tocurrency that was accessible at the time, (b) the dilutive =E2=80=98minti=
ng=E2=80=99 of approximately $300 million in FTT tokens by an unauthorized =
source after the Petition Date and (c) the failure of the co-founders and p=
otentially others to identify additional wallets believed to contain Debtor=
 assets.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In seeking rescue financing, Bankman-Fried <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29730538.256530/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4LXMt=
YmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTcyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWR=
pdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTExNyZ1dG1fY2FtcG=
FpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB663fb68d" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  circulate=
d a rough balance sheet</a> showing about $9 billion of customer deposits. =
Against that $9 billion of deposits, FTX=E2=80=99s liquidators have found a=
bout $740 million of cryptocurrency, not counting the hundreds of millions =
of dollars of cryptocurrency that were drained from FTX=E2=80=99s poorly se=
cured wallets when it filed for bankruptcy. They have also found about $564=
 million in cash, though, =E2=80=9Cbecause of historical cash management fa=
ilures, the Debtors do not yet know the exact amount of cash that the FTX G=
roup held as of the Petition Date.=E2=80=9D There=E2=80=99s some crypto, th=
ere=E2=80=99s some cash, nobody quite knows how much, but it=E2=80=99s pret=
ty clear that the basic answer is =E2=80=9Cnot nearly enough.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are other assets. There is a <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29730538.256530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTYvZnR4LWxhdGVzdC1iYW5r=
bWFuLWZyaWVkLWFkbWl0cy1lcnJvci1hcy1jb25ncmVzcy1wbGFucy1wcm9iZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQ=
xMTE3MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlci=
Z1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMTcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBd850b116" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  $1 billion personal loan</a> from Alameda to Sam Ba=
nkman-Fried, for instance?=C2=A0Also, though, Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s rough=
 balance sheet showed $3.2 billion in illiquid private investments, includi=
ng $1.5 billion in =E2=80=9Cother ventures.=E2=80=9D Those investments are,=
 in theory, assets that are available to pay off creditors. Here is how Ray=
 describes those investments:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FTX Group had billions in investments othe=
r than cryptocurrency, as suggested above in the descriptions of the four S=
ilos. However, the main companies in the Alameda Silo and the Ventures Silo=
 did not keep complete books and records of their investments and activitie=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors are creating a balance sheet and o=
ther financial statements for the Alameda Silo and the Ventures Silo as of =
the Petition Date. The Debtors are doing so from the =E2=80=98bottom-up=E2=
=80=99 by using the records of cash transactions at the Debtors, and also a=
re reviewing various third-party sources to locate investments.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine being the new CEO of a giant investing=
 firm, and coming in to work your first day and asking your employees: =E2=
=80=9CSo, what investments have we invested in?=E2=80=9D And they answer: =
=E2=80=9C<em>I don=E2=80=99t know, why don=E2=80=99t you Google it, maybe t=
here are some newspaper articles about the investments we made</em>.=E2=80=
=9D =E2=80=9CReviewing various third-party sources to locate investments=E2=
=80=9D! FTX/Alameda made investments and=C2=A0<em>didn=E2=80=99t write them=
 down</em>, but maybe somebody=C2=A0<em>else=C2=A0</em>kept track of what t=
hey own.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-colo=
r: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> What.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But all this stuff about FTX=C2=A0<em>barely k=
eeping track of its assets </em>is somehow less bad than the stuff about FT=
X=C2=A0<em>not keeping track of its liabilities at all</em>. As part of his=
 declaration, Ray presents unaudited September balance sheets of each of th=
e FTX silos, though he presents them mostly for entertainment purposes: =E2=
=80=9CBecause such balance sheet was=C2=A0produced while the Debtors were c=
ontrolled by Mr. Bankman-Fried, I do not have confidence in it, and the inf=
ormation therein may not be correct as of the date stated.=E2=80=9D They do=
n=E2=80=99t correspond particularly closely to the recently publicized resc=
ue balance sheet, and I am not going to discuss them further. Except to quo=
te a footnote that appears on the balance sheets for the exchange businesse=
s: =E2=80=9CCustomer custodial fund assets are comprised of fiat customer d=
eposit balances. Balances of customer crypto assets deposited are not prese=
nted.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Ray writes<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The WRS Silo Debtors are expected =
to have significant liabilities arising from crypto assets deposited by cus=
tomers through the FTX US platform. However, such liabilities are not refle=
cted in the financial statements prepared while these companies were under =
the control of Mr. Bankman-Fried.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could look at that and say =E2=80=9Cwell, =
that=E2=80=99s fine, they didn=E2=80=99t include customer assets on their b=
alance sheets because those assets didn=E2=80=99t belong to them, this is r=
easonable; the customer assets were tracked separately and not viewed as co=
rporate assets.=E2=80=9D Except it seems quite clear that FTX=C2=A0<em>did=
=C2=A0</em>use customer assets for its own (or Alameda=E2=80=99s) purposes,=
 that it didn=E2=80=99t just <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29730538.256530/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDkvYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1zLWZ0eC1oYWQtYS1kZWF0aC1zcGlyYWw=
tYmVmb3JlLWJpbmFuY2UtZGVhbD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTE3MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMTcmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa5303521" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  keep them s=
afe in a box</a> until customers asked for them back. If the story here was=
 =E2=80=9CFTX made use of customer assets, recording them as assets on its =
balance sheet with an offsetting liability to customers, and then it lost t=
he assets, oops,=E2=80=9D that would not be=C2=A0<em>great=C2=A0</em>or any=
thing. But you could=C2=A0<em>understand=C2=A0</em>it, not in the moral sen=
se of like =E2=80=9Coh I understand why they did that=E2=80=9D but just in =
the cognitive sense of, like, you could look at a balance sheet and say =E2=
=80=9Cah see that=E2=80=99s where the money went.=E2=80=9D Here FTX has som=
e balance sheets that list some assets and liabilities, but they don=E2=80=
=99t list the only liabilities that really matter: what FTX owes to its cus=
tomers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m being a little unfair, and presuma=
bly there is some system that tracks customer liabilities and that Ray can =
use to reconstruct what is owed to customers. But for now he doesn=E2=80=99=
t list, or even estimate, the customer liabilities. And he says that the FT=
X companies =E2=80=9Care unable to create a list of their top 50 creditors =
that includes customers=E2=80=9D right now, because that data is =E2=80=9Ci=
n repositories that have been the subject of unauthorized attempts to acces=
s,=E2=80=9D and so FTX has =E2=80=9Cimplemented certain defensive measures.=
=E2=80=9D The CEO is =E2=80=A6 locked out of looking at the customer accoun=
ts because too many hackers are also trying to look at them?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, on Tuesday night Kelsey Piper at Vox exc=
hanged some Twitter direct messages with Sam Bankman-Fried; Vox=C2=A0<a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29730538.256530/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cudm94LmNvbS9mdXR1cmUtcGVyZmVjdC8yMzQ2MjMzMy9zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1=
mdHgtY3J5cHRvY3VycmVuY3ktZWZmZWN0aXZlLWFsdHJ1aXNtLWNyeXB0by1iYWhhbWFzLXBoaW=
xhbnRocm9weQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB34790b9f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">published them yest=
erday and=C2=A0they are quite something</a>. They include some some discuss=
ion of how FTX sent its customers=E2=80=99 money over to Alameda, which the=
n lost it, though his answers here are not super-clear. (He =E2=80=9Cthough=
t Alameda had enough collateral to reasonably cover it,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=
=9Cmessy accounting + margin exchange =E2=86=92=C2=A0position built up over=
 time.=E2=80=9D) But there is also some discussion about how FTX could have=
=C2=A0<em>forgotten about=C2=A0</em>$8 billion of customer liabilities:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">like, =E2=80=9Coh FTX doesn=E2=80=99t have a b=
ank account, I guess people can wire to Alameda=E2=80=99s to get money on F=
TX.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=A6=C2=A03 years later =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9Coh [no] it looks like people wired $8=
b to Alameda and oh god we basically forgot about the stub account that cor=
responded to that and so it was never delivered to FTX.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Honestly I think that if I started a gigantic =
financial exchange with my college buddies I would not mess <em>this=C2=A0<=
/em>one up, but who knows. The point here is: Does FTX even know what it ow=
es to customers? I cannot feel 100% confident, either from Ray=E2=80=99s de=
claration or from those DMs, that the answer is yes.</p>
