f4b8524a319a23cB1e3f8e94" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> FTX=E2=80=99s employees=E2=80=99 reactio=
n to the bankruptcy</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What started as a dream job turned into a nigh=
tmare for employees of FTX, the crypto exchange that imploded in spectacula=
r fashion last week. The Wall Street Journal spoke to more than a dozen cur=
rent and former employees, many of whom said they were stunned by FTX=E2=80=
=99s swift demise and shocked by the alleged misuse of customer funds. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ryan Salame, co-chief executive of the exchang=
e=E2=80=99s Bahamas-based unit FTX Digital Markets, told people close to hi=
m that he became physically sick and threw up when he became aware of FTX=
=E2=80=99s problems early last week, the people said. Although he worked cl=
osely with Mr. Bankman-Fried, Mr. Salame wasn=E2=80=99t part of the inner c=
ircle around FTX=E2=80=99s leader, the people said. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dozens of FTX employees quit last week, includ=
ing senior figures such as head of product Ramnik Arora, chief regulatory o=
fficer Dan Friedberg and head of institutional sales Zane Tackett, people f=
amiliar with the matter said. One employee said he submitted his resignatio=
n to his boss, only for the boss to say he had already resigned himself.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A friend of Mr. Friedberg=E2=80=99s who had di=
nner with him the day he quit said the attorney=E2=80=94previously a big ad=
mirer of Mr. Bankman-Fried=E2=80=94was visibly shaken.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Friedberg showed this friend the text mess=
age he sent to Mr. Bankman-Fried and other top FTX executives submitting hi=
s resignation. In the message, the friend recalled, Mr. Friedberg described=
 himself as devastated and said: =E2=80=9COne day I hope I can forgive you.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the one hand, it does seem like FTX was wha=
t you=E2=80=99d get if a half-dozen college buddies ran a global financial =
exchange with no supervision. On the other hand, there were in fact hundred=
s of employees, including a chief regulatory officer. They resigned in shoc=
k when they learned about FTX=E2=80=99s insolvency and its misuse of custom=
er money. But presumably they knew about the =E2=80=A6=C2=A0emojis in the c=
hats? It is one thing for a small group of top executives, who all live wit=
h each other, to do intentional fraud and keep it secret from the rest of t=
he company. But the =E2=80=9Ccomplete failure of corporate controls and =E2=
=80=A6 complete absence of trustworthy financial information=E2=80=9D seems=
 like something someone might have noticed.</p>
